<section xml:id="sec_absolute_value_function">
  <title>Absolute Value Function</title>
  <p>
        <idx><h>mathematical functions</h><h>absolute value</h></idx>
  </p>
  <p>
    The absolute value function in Maple can be typed out using the <c>abs()</c> command.
    There is also an absolute value button under the Expression palette if you prefer that method.
  </p>
  <p>
    \begin{maplegroup} \begin{mapleinput} {abs(a); } \end{mapleinput} \relax \begin{maplelatex} {abs(a)}{
    <me>
      \displaystyle {|a|}
    </me>
  </p>
  <p>
    } <idx><h>mathematical functions</h><h>absolute value</h></idx> \end{maplelatex} \end{maplegroup}
  </p>
</section>